```kotlin
class HomeViewModelFactory @Inject constructor(
    // Inject your dependencies here
) : ViewModelProvider.Factory {
    override fun &lt;T : ViewModel?&gt; create(modelClass: Class&lt;T&gt;): T {
        if (modelClass.isAssignableFrom(HomeViewModel::class.java)) {
            @Suppress(&quot;UNCHECKED_CAST&quot;)
            return HomeViewModel(
                // Pass the injected dependencies here
            ) as T
        }
        throw IllegalArgumentException(&quot;Unknown ViewModel class&quot;)
    }
}
```

2. Ensure you have a Dagger module set up to provide the dependencies required by `HomeViewModel` and `HomeViewModelFactory`.

```kotlin
@Module
class AppModule {
    // Provide your dependencies here
}
```

3. Update your `HomescreenFragment` to use the ViewModel with the custom factory for proper dependency injection.

```kotlin
class HomescreenFragment : BaseMvRxFragment() {

    @Inject
    lateinit var viewModelFactory: HomeViewModelFactory

    private val parentViewModel: HomeViewModel by viewModels { viewModelFactory }

    // ...
}
```

By following these steps, your app should no longer crash, and you&#39;ll be able to use `parentViewModel` with its dependencies correctly injected. Ensure that your Dagger setup is providing the dependencies as required.

